vs. 24.5 ± 9.2 kg, p = 0.001). Multiple regression analysis showed significant 
association between 6-min walking distance change and postoperative physical 
functioning scores of health-related quality of life (p = 0.036).
CONCLUSION: The results suggest that motor function decreases postoperatively, 
and a decrease in 6-min walking distance after surgery is associated with 
postoperative physical functioning in patients with pancreatic cancer.

